50|$|Liverpool {{reached their}} first League Cup final in 1978 and this {{occasion}} was to prove memorable for McDermott {{for the wrong}} reasons. The first game at Wembley against Nottingham Forest F.C. ended goalless, but McDermott had a goal disallowed after the officials decided that teammate Kenny Dalglish was in an offside position when McDermott struck his shot. In the replay at Old Trafford, after Forest had opened the scoring with a hotly disputed penalty, McDermott scored {{what he thought was}} the equaliser with a well-struck drive, only for the officials to deny him again, claiming he had controlled the pass with his arm. Forest held on to win 1-0 and McDermott offered <b>to</b> <b>swear</b> <b>on</b> <b>oath</b> in an after-match interview that he had trapped the ball legally with his chest.|$|E
